    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"5-49\">\n<h2>5-49</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 7, Section 1: Recognizing Growth &amp; Decay</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Classifies bouncing-ball data and a sequence as exponential/geometric decay.</div>\n<div class=\"contentContainerReference-body\"><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-9\"><p class=\"\">Chelsea dropped a bouncy ball off the roof while Nery recorded its rebound height. The table at right shows their data. Note that the $0$ in the “Bounce” column represents the starting height. </p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p class=\"\">To what family does the function belong? Explain how you know.</p></li><li><p class=\"\">Show the data as a sequence. Is the sequence arithmetic, geometric, quadratic, or something else? Justify your answer.</p></li></ol></div><div class=\"col-sm-3 col-align-top\"><table><tbody><tr><th><p class=\"\">Bounce</p></th><th><p class=\"\">Rebound<br/> Height</p></th></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$0$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$800$ cm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$1$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$475$ cm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$2$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$290$ cm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$3$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$175$ cm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$4$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$100$ cm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$5$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$60$ cm</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div>\n</section>",
